5,"rs":146,"damage":147},"Two single lines of text, one on the left and one on the right side. Both texts run left to right, and so the text on the left runs from the rear of the stone to the front, while the text on the right runs from the front to the back. The text on the left is missing the opening letters, having been inscribed prior to the removal of the 'step' from the rear of the stone. The text on the right appears to be essentially intact.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"ana":148},"#text_condition.complete",{"lettering":150,"dimensions":151},"Both texts employ ligatures.",[152,156],{"type":35,"l":36,"from":37,"to":37,"h":153,"unit":38,"atLeast":154,"atMost":155},"30-35","30","35",{"type":40,"l":41,"from":37,"to":42,"unit":38},{"_":158,"notBefore":159,"notAfter":159,"evidence":160},"Explicitly dated to the consulship of 108 CE",108,"office",[162,165],{"_":163,"type":50,"ref":164,"region":2},"Tauromenium","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462506",{"_":166,"type":55,"ref":167,"region":2},"Taormina","http://sws.geonames.org/2522975",[169],[170,171],37.85358,15.28851,[173,174],37.85237,15.292201,{"_":176,"role":66,"ref":177},"Antiquarium del Teatro Antico","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/062",{"_":179,"type":70},"3555",{"_":72,"mainLang":73,"languages":181},[72],"491492",[184],{"atLeast":185,"atMost":186},30,35,[87,188,94,90,189],"Lo Faso Pietrasanta (Duca di Serradifalco), 1832-1842, Antichita Siciliane esplorate ed illustrate","Muscolino, 2023, A block of marmor luculleum/africano in the ancient theatre of Taormina (CIL, X, 6996) with notae lapicidinarum (AD 108)",[98,191,105,101,192],"EMAB7PTB","FUT4TN9H",[194,195,196,130,134,138,197,198,112,113,198,199,116,73],"isic000284","block of marmor luculleum bearing quarry inscription",{"_":12},"tauromenium","taormina","antiquarium del teatro antico","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Cspan class=\"textpartnumber\">face 1\u003C/span>  \u003Ca id=\"al